  "commentary": "**Dealer Hedging Commentary:**\n\nWith SPX spot at 6605 sitting directly on the max positive gamma wall (+52144.1M), dealers are aggressively selling into any rallies above this level while simultaneously providing buying support at the 6590 negative gamma floor (-25077.4M). The PIN regime with massive positive GEX concentration between 6605-6620 creates a strong gravitational pull keeping price anchored near current levels, with dealers acting as stabilizers rather than momentum amplifiers. Watch 6608 GEX flip as the key inflection point—below this level expect dealer buying pressure to intensify, while any break above triggers systematic selling into the thick 6610-6620 resistance zone.\n\n**Bottom line:** Price should stay pinned in a tight range between 6590-6610 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
